# Kids App Design System

## Reference

Approved reference: `child-pin` PIN screen — coral / salmon through golden orange, white type, glass circular keypad.

## Screen background (CRITICAL)

- The root `(child)/_layout.tsx` applies `LinearGradient` with `COLORS.kids.gradientApp` as `StyleSheet.absoluteFill`.
- Each screen's outer `SafeAreaView` / `View` must use `backgroundColor: 'transparent'` so the shell gradient shows.
- For routes outside `(child)` (e.g. `link-device`, `child-pin`), wrap with `KidsGradientScreen` or repeat the same gradient pattern.

## Text on gradient

- `COLORS.kids.textOnGradient` and `textOnGradientMuted` for hero copy on the gradient; avoid `#1E293B` / `#1e1b4b` for text sitting directly on the gradient background.

## Glass controls

- `COLORS.kids.glassButtonBg`, `glassButtonBorder`, `glassButtonText`; use `KidsGlassButton` where a circular / pill key matches the PIN keypad.

## Tab bar

- `tabBarActive` white, `tabBarInactive` semi-transparent white; `tabBarBg` light coral tint.

## Do NOT

- Do not use full-screen cream / violet tints (`#F7F5FF`, `#F8F4FF`, `#FFF8F0`) as the **root** screen fill — they block the shared gradient. Use `transparent` on the root; cards may use `rgba(255,255,255,0.88)`.
- Do not use parent indigo (`#6366F1`) on kid flows.
